"v.揭穿真相，暴露 【英】 v. 揭穿真相，暴露(to expose the false or exaggerated claims) 【记】 de+bunk(岸bank)→去 掉河岸→暴露 【例】 A lot of people used to believe that, but now it's been quite thoroughly debunked. v. 揭穿真相; 暴露出(虚假、哄骗或吹嘘) 【记】de去掉, bunk = bank岸－去掉岸－暴露(洪水)de去掉, bunk = bank银行－暴露(出金库) 【反】perpetuate to sham(永远的伪装); unexposure(v 不揭露) 【记】bunk 铺位，床；debunk 把床揭露出来；de + bank把银行揭露出来；音：绷开，穿绷 debunk (v.)  1923,  from de- + bunk (n.2); first used by U.S. novelist William Woodward (1874-1950), the notion being ""to take the bunk out of things.""  Related: Debunked; debunking."
